Here is a ntr engine design described briefly from the middle 1970s.<br>
<br>
 You have fuel  rods of perhaps 10% pure U 235 metal. You place them inside of hollow tubes inside of a cylindrical core of  beryllium metal. The beryllium metal also has propellant tubes  drilled through it, next two the holes for the fuel rods. It also has  other tubes in wich boron control rods  are inserted. If I use 5000 kilograms of the ten percent enriched uranium as fuel , I can assembe the equivelent of up to<br>
25 critical masses in the core <br>
<br>
 A hexaganal pattern is used in which each fuel rod is surrounded by 4 symmetrical propellant tubes. This reactor core resembles a honeycomb inside of a bee hive. There are control rods placed between the hexagonal fuel rod,propellant tube clusters.The  beryllium /uranium reactor core is placed<br>
inside of a massive thick steel casing which serves as the<br>
nuclear radiation shield. At the top of the core is a propellant injector which injects Liquid hydrogen into the core.<br>
<br>
 The hydrogen goes through the core and is heated to from 2000 to 2500 degrees celcius.Then the hydrogen leaves the core and is expelled through a 45 degree converging/diverging delaval nozzle.Before the hydrogen is injected into the core it goes through a regenerative cooling jacket around the casing , and the delaval nozzle. <br>
<br>
 This is a phoebus class ntr solid core motor, that can generate from 200,000 to 400,000 pounds of thrust with a specific impulse of from 800 to 1000 seconds.This class of ntr engine was tested from 1967 to 1972 at jackass flats in nevada by the the los alamos laboratory. In 1973 it was ready for live flight testing as an upper stage on a chemical rocket when the U.S  congress stopped funding the nerva project.<br>
<br>
<br>
The boron control rods are controled by electric motors.<br>
They control the nuetron cross section of the reactor.<br>
By taking away neutrons when you drop the rods into the core<br>
the fission reaction is stopped or slowed down By removing the rods the neutron flux is increased to start the engine  or speed up the fission reaction in the core. Thermionic diodes can tap radioactive decay heat from the core and convert it directly into electric power when the reactor is shut down by the control rods. This will generate about 400 watts for each pound of the engines fuel weight . 5000 kilograms of 10% heu<br>
can thus generate about 4.8 megawatts of electric power<br>
24/7 for the next 10,000 years or so.This can run a 10,000<br>
second specific ipulse ion drive which can accelerate close to 1 gram of ions per second to 100,000 meters per second or so.<br>
This is also how to make a bi-mode atomic propulsion system.<br>
This system was origionally intended to carry people to land on mars by around the year 1980, and build a base there.<br>
